<TD WIDTH=350 valign=bottom align=left><font face="arial, helvetica" size=2><b>
<img src="war_ia.gif" width=21 height=46 align=left vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0>punched the elevator button on the eighth floor of the fantasy tower at ceasar’s palace in las vegas. ding. the doors slid open to reveal two praetorian guards in full dress uniform. they were drop-dead serious and totally for real. well, as real as anything gets in las vegas.
<p>
<a href="war_3.html"><img src="war_3_sm.jpg" width=200 height=119 align=right vspace=6 hspace=0 border=0></a>
there they stood, holding spears, bright red brush topping their helmets. gold breastplates, shinguards — two beefed-out ’roid boyz, better than 400 pounds on the hoof, er, sandals. they nodded and i got on board, standing between them for the non-stop ride to the lobby.</td>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=550 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=15>
<TD WIDTH=401 valign=bottom align=left><font face="arial, helvetica" size=2><b>
