<a href="war_8.html"><img src="war_8_sm.jpg" width=178 height=200 align=left vspace=6 hspace=0 border=0></a> 
but it was swell fun while it lasted. for three minutes and 18 seconds, i enjoyed one of the principal perks of the emperor game: an imperial roman bodyguard detail.
<p>
i remembered that day when i first saw these images by giovanni rufo, an italian photographer with a keen sense of opera. his men could be stars in the palace of any ceasar, in nevada or in rome.</td>
<TD WIDTH=149 valign=top align=center>
<a href="war_9.html"><img src="war_9_sm.jpg" width=149 height=295 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a></td>
