<font face="arial, helvetica" size=2>
<b>sadao hasegawa is japanese, but his work is increasingly influenced by more primal asian cutures. drawing from sexual and erotic cult symbolism found in bali, thailand and cambodia, hasegawa’s pouched men wear variations of the <i>fundoshi,</i> the japanese posing strap. 
<p>
illustrations of erect cocks and pubic hair are outlawed in mainstream japanese publishing. but hasegawa draws on generations of asian artists who’ve used the shape of the pouch to define, in negative space, the dimensions of the man’s anatomy.
<p>
sadao hasegawa’s work can be seen in <u>sadao hasegawa, paintings and drawings</u>, published by editions aubrey walter, gmp, publishers, london.</b></td></table>
