<TD  valign=top align=left>
<FONT face="arial, helvetica" SIZE=2 color="#6B8BB0"><b>three years ago, patrick perez picked up his camera and conidered photography again. as a little kid, he had been bitten by the shutterbug — school science fair project and
all. but decades ago, perez had packed it all away, dismissing photography as a fond memory, a boy thing. <BR><BR>
in reality, photography was a time bomb, ticking away in this mild-mannered southern california native. long after growing up in ventura county, long after the university of california at santa barbara, perez picked up his camera and began shooting more men than a disgruntled postal employee.<BR><BR>
his only formal training was a high school photography class (strictly a black-and-white experience). but this time,
perez approached photography with a deeper resource — the years he'd studied psychology. <BR><BR>
he'd considered being a therapist and was on the road to having his own practice. but in patrick perez, photography and psychology morphed into a probe-on-film of the psyches of the men he photographs.<BR><BR>
in three years, perez has produced a massive volume of work. his magazine credits include <i>playgirl, for women only, hx</i> and <i>edge.</i> his work is found in seven calendars for 1997. his images save screens on computers worldwide with his ‘men on disk,’ cd-rom. perez also produced the <i>men’s swimsuit video review</i> launching an original home video genre.</B></td></table>


<TABLE WIDTH=560 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=15>
<TD WIDTH=325 valign=top align=right>
<FONT face="arial, helvetica" SIzE=2 color="#6B8BB0"><b>perez is a solid television producer with eleven emmy award nominations to his name, but video isn’t his favorite medium. the magnitude of a video shoot crew overwhelms the intimacy of one man, one camera, one model — alone. for perez, photography is an exercise in intimacy.<BR><BR>
‘i thrive on the challenge of igniting of the creative spark in a model,’ says perez over enchiladas at tia juana’s on l.a.’s westside. ‘it’s the psychology of revelation. i want to be part of the process.’<BR><BR>
to do that, perez prefers to develop fresh talent — the pros can get blazé. he invests time getting to know the man under the muscle and even helps new talent launch and manage their careers.<BR><BR>
when it’s all down on film, perez shows the world a moment in time in the life of a man, and usually a feeling pure enough to be an icon of masculinity.</td>
<TD WIDTH=225 valign=middle align=bottom>
<A HREF="perez_chris5.html"><img src="perez_chris5_sm.jpg" width=225 height=192
align=bottom vspace=5 hspace=0 border=0></a><br>
