<META Name="description" Content="Men in their Underwear: Hanging out with the Swim Team">
<HEAD>
<title>men in their underwear · swim team</title>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#5AAAE0" LINK="#FF6D60" VLINK="#789278" ALINK="#FFFFFF">


<BODY>
<br><br>
<blockquote>
<TABLE WIDTH=227 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=5>
<TD VALIGN=bottom WIDTH=189 ALIGN=right><img src="mitu_small_a.gif" 
width=189 height=65 align=left vspace=0 border=0 hspace=0></td>
<TD VALIGN=bottom WIDTH=38 ALIGN=left>
<a href="swim.html"><img src="jump.gif" 
width=38 height=30 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a></td></table>
</blockquote><br><br>
<center>


<TABLE WIDTH=536 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=10>
<TD WIDTH=156 valign=top align=right><br><br>
<a href="swimteam1.html">
<img src="lenzie2-sm.jpg" width=156 height=289
align=bottom vspace=4 hspace=0 border=0></a>
<p>
<a href="swimteam2.html">
<img src="penstate_sm.jpg" width=156 height=103
align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a>
<br><br>
<img src="swim_foster.jpg" width=156 height=292
align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></td>

<TD VALIGN=top width=370 ALIGN=left>
<img src="swimguys.jpg" width=200 height=293
align=left vspace=4 hspace=0 border=0 alt="">
<br><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#8B8670" size=2><b>
olympic diving is rooted in the sport of gymnastics. competitive diving was born in the 17th century when gymnasts in sweden and germany practiced their sport over water on equipment set up on the beaches each summer. by the late 19th century the new sport of diving was born. as late as the 1920s, diving events were included in gymnastic competitions. the first recorded diving competition was held in 1893 in england with a ‘plunging’ championship. 
<br><br>
diving made its olympic debut in 1904 at st. louis with a men's springboard competition won by g. e. sheldon of the united states. american competitors have dominated olympic diving since sheldon’s triumph in 1904. from the ten-meter platform a diver is traveling about 35 miles per hour when he enters the water.
<br><br>
<img src="dumais1.jpg" width=109 height=190
align=right vspace=4 hspace=0 border=0 alt="">
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#8B8670" size=2><b>
swimmers race to see who can touch the wall first. the pool is 50 meters long and distances range from 50 meters to 1,500 meters. in individual medleys, swimmers do each stroke — butterfly, backstroke, breaststroke and freestyle, in that order. in relays, swimmers must not leave the blocks before their teammate touches the wall. 
<br><br>
before competition, swimmers shave their bodies and heads because it reduces the resistance between skin and water — and as a ritual to evoke the warrior spirit.<br><p>
<a href="swimteam3.html"><img src="grote_sm.jpg" width=160 height=104
align=left vspace=4 hspace=0 border=0></a><a href="swimteam4.html"><img src="swim_polo_sm.jpg" width=160 height=76
align=bottomt vspace=4 hspace=0 border=0></a></td></TABLE>
<br><br><br><br>


