<a href="dupre_space.html"><img src="dupre_space.jpg" width=200 height=126 align=bottom vspace=0 border=0 hspace=0></a></td>
<TD width=250 valign=top align=left>
<font face="arial, helvetica" size=2><b>stéphane dupré was born in paris in 1960. he began illustrating as a boy and entered the well-known ecoule boulle to study furniture design and decoration and later moved into graphic arts.<p>

dupré’s career has included advertising — as well as illustration for the french gay press including the magazines <i>illico</i> and <i>double face</i>.<p>

dupré’s work is mostly stippled illustration, though unlike rex and many others who work in the style, dupré often colors his work. his backdrops are usually solid color fields, historic props and cultural icons for the erotic themes which he explores.<p>

<a href="dupre_twins.html"><img src="dupre_2boys.jpg" width=200 height=320 align=bottom vspace=0 border=0 hspace=0></a><p>
they are exceptional illustrations that cover acres of emotional ground. but what if dupré’s these sex-charged boys were to escape from their paper reality and land in our world?<p>

we have relocated dupré’s men into photographic settings from etruscan tombs to modern shipyards — even cambodian torture cells.<p>

the worlds of fantasy and reality collide, producing a new hybrid, a fresh, new alternative universe. click any image on this page to explore those worlds on your own.</td></table>
