<HEAD>
<title>men in their underwear · photos by jason meyers</title>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#B8B8A1" LINK="#BAA55E" VLINK="#BAA55E" ALINK="#FFFFFF">
<embed src="mid_jason.mid" autostart="true" loop="true" hidden="true">

<br><br>

<blockquote>
<TABLE WIDTH=227 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=5>
<TD VALIGN=bottom WIDTH=189 ALIGN=right><img src="mitu_small_a.gif" width=189 height=65 align=left vspace=0 border=0 hspace=0></td>
<TD VALIGN=bottom WIDTH=38 ALIGN=left>
<a href="2.html"><img src="jump.gif" width=38 height=30 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a></td></table>
</blockquote>
<br>

<center>

<TABLE WIDTH=422 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TD WIDTH=225 valign=middle align=right>
<img src="jason_head.gif" width=225 height=78 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></td>
<TD WIDTH=197 valign=top align=left><a href="jason2.html"><img src="jason2_sm.jpg" width=197 height=332 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a></td>
</TABLE>

<br><br>

<TABLE WIDTH=370 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TD WIDTH=200 valign=top align=right><blockquote><font face="arial, helvetica" size=2><b>there is something about the way jason meyers sees youth that distinguishes his work from the rest. ‘i guess you’d say i’m looking for the beauty of it,’ he says. jason’s work documents the fresh world of modern boys. at 28, jason is a peer among them.<br><br>
</blockquote>
<a href="jason10.html"><img src="jason10_sm.jpg" width=200 height=143 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a>
<blockquote>
‘there’s a new feeling out there,’ says jason from philadelphia, his home town. ‘these days, the natural look is in.’ <p>point taken. boomers and gen-xers fell into a major body culture thing until it shone with a clone veneer. jason’s dudes are their little brothers, all grown up and looking at life, physicality and sexuality way differently.</td>
<TD WIDTH=170 valign=top align=left><a href="jason4.html"><img src="jason4_sm.jpg" width=170 height=259 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a><a href="jason6.html"><img src="jason6_sm.jpg" width=170 height=270 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a><p><font face="arial, helvetica" size=2 color="#7E99B3"><b><blockquote><i>‘i’d love to do more outside work, but philadelphia’s not the best place for that. maybe i’ll move to d.c.’</i></td>
</TABLE>

<br><br>

<TABLE WIDTH=360 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TD WIDTH=160 valign=top align=right>
<a href="jason3.html"><img src="jason3_sm.jpg" width=160 height=225 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a><br>
<a href="jason8.html"><img src="jason8_sm.jpg" width=160 height=319 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a><p>
<blockquote><font face="arial, helvetica" size=2 color="#B28681"><b><i>‘i’m planning on using my computer more for enhancing the photographs. well, to de-enhance them, really.’<br><br>
<font color="#7E997C">‘for me it began just fooling around with a camera when I was 15 or 16, but I didn’t start erotic photography until I was 20. my favorite then, and now, is bruce weber ’cause he shows beauty in a sensual way.’</i></td>
<TD WIDTH=200 valign=top align=left><blockquote><font face="arial, helvetica" size=2><b>in jason’s work you see a new generation at ease in its own reality, not through the perceptions of a photographer from another mindset. ‘i give my models a lot of freedom to have fun and be themselves,’ says jason, who likes to work with first time models. jason gets his images by letting college guys be themselves.<br><br><br>
</blockquote>
<a href="jason1.html"><img src="jason1_sm.jpg" width=175 height=242 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a><br><a href="jason7.html"><img src="jason7_sm.jpg" width=200 height=135 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0></a><br><p>
<blockquote>
<br>jason’s work represents the next big thing, and though he doesn’t seek fashion assignments, it would be just like fashion to find jason meyers.<br><br><a href="http://newwaveimages.com/artists/JMirada/Gallery1.html" target="_blank.">gallery prints</a> are available on <a href="http://newwaveimages.com/artists/JMeyers.html" target="_blank">jason’s web site</a> and he’s seeking new photo subjects. <a href="mailto:Meyersj@NewWaveImages.com">send him email</a>. jason meyers has his lens focused on tomorrow — today.</td></TABLE><br>
<hr size=1 width=360>
<font face="arial, helvetica" size=2 color="#7E99B3"><b>to see the work of other photographers, visit our <a href="arts.html">photo galleries</a><br><br><br><br>
</center>
</body>
