<HTML>

<HEAD>
<title>BERSERKISTAN IN BOSNIA: Berserkistan's Wired</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#454545" link="#A62A2A" vlink="#B87333">

<BODY>

<center>
<hr size=1 width=280>
<img src="flat280.jpg" align=bottom alt=BERSERKISTAN>
<hr size=1 width=280>

<a href="berserk.html"><img src="b_berser.gif" alt="Main Menu" align=middle border=0></a>
<a href="travel.html"><img src="b_travel.gif" alt="Travel" align=middle border=0></a>
<a href="journal.html"><img src="b_journ.gif" alt="Journal" align=middle border=0></a><br>
<a href="bosbg.html"><img src="b_brief.gif" alt="Briefing" vspace=4  align=middle border=0></a>
<a href="/bosmap.html"><img src="b_map.gif" alt="Troop Map" vspace=4 align=middle border=0></a>
<a href="links.html"><img src="b_links.gif" alt="World Links" vspace=4 align=middle border=0></a><br>



<br><br><br>

<font size=4><b>
Berserkistan's Wired.</b>
<img src="wired_b.jpg" alt="Wired, April 96" width=175 height=220 vspace=0 align=bottom border=0><br>
<img src="wired_a.jpg" alt="Page 36" width=500 height=271 vspace=4 align=middle border=0>
<font size=2>
</center>
<blockquote>
<blockquote>
<font size=1>Wired, April 1996, Page 36 . . .<p>
<font size=4><b>World Wide War</b><br>
<font size=2>Berserkistan is the home of a newfangled kind of war reporting, conjured up by photojournalist Jim Bartlett. Netizens already expect to be able to correspond with reporters, but Bartlett goes one step further by providing the Net addresses of the people featured in his electronic dispatches from Bosnia. He also offers free homepages to Balkan Residents. By the time you read this, video and auido feeds from Sarajevo and Tuzls should be a staple at the site.
<p>
Bartlett, who is Berserkistan's founder and editor in chief, is no stranger ot the region. He's spent more than 20 months there, covering the war. However new his distribution medium, Bartlett's philosophy is grounded in Robert Capa's old addage: "If your pictures aren't good enough, you're not close enough." Find out how close he can get at <a href="berserk.html"><i>www.linder.com/berserk/berserk.html.</i></a><br>
&#151;Rogier van Bakel<br><br><br>

</blockquote>
Berserkistan is the world news service of<br> 
<a href="/index.html">
Pacific Interactive Media Corp.</a><br>
<a href="mailto=mlinder@linder.com">EMail Berserkistan</a><br>
<font size=1>&#169;1996, All Rights Reserved
<br>
