<br>
<hr size=1 align=left>

<TABLE WIDTH=550 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=15>
<TD WIDTH=88 valign=top align=right>
<font size=1>
<img src="navigator.gif" USEMAP="#navigator" 
width=80 height=256 alt="Berserkistan Navigator" hspace=0 
vspace=2 align=bottom border=0></td>

<TD valign=top align=left>
<font size=6><b>Matej Vipotnik</b><br>
<font size=3>Berserkistan Special Correspondent<p>
<font size=2>
<img src="matej2.gif" alt="Matej Vipotnik" align=left hspace=8 width=262 height=201>Matej Vipotnik was born in Slovenia in 1975. He spent his early years there, and in Italy, before coming to the United States as a student at Boston University in 1993.
<p>
Matej is currently enrolled in the International Relations program at BU and became a Berserkistan reader while enrolled in the EPIIC Program at Tufts University. There, he is involved in Multimedia projects concerning international themes. The EPIIC's current project is a CD-ROM entitled, "Cities of Intolerance," which examines the social and physical reconstruction of divided cities such as Beirut, Belfast, Jerusalem and Sarajevo.
<p>
This summer, Matej was sent to the Balkans to do research for the project and has agreed to document his travels for Berserkistan as a special correspondent.
</td></table>

