<HEAD>
<title>BERSERKISTAN IN BOSNIA: Departing Commander Honored by NATO</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#454545" link="#A62A2A" vlink="#B87333">

<BODY>
<blockquote>
<img src="flat280.gif" width=280 height=119 
align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 alt="BERSERKISTAN">
<br>
<hr size=1 align=left>

<TABLE WIDTH=550 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=15>
<TD WIDTH=88 valign=top align=right>
<font size=1>
<img src="navigator.gif" USEMAP="#navigator" 
width=80 height=256 alt="Berserkistan Navigator" hspace=0 
vspace=2 align=bottom border=0></td>

<TD valign=top align=left>
<FONT SIZE=5><b>
Departing NATO Commander<br>
Adm. Leighton Smith<br> 
Honored with NATO Medal</b>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=3><b>
‘You have made an outstanding contribution<br> 
to peace on this continent’</b><br>
<FONT SIZE=2>
—NATO Secretary-General Javier Solana
<p>

<font size=2><img src="lsmith_lg.gif" width=160 height=200 align=left vspace=3 alt="Admiral Leighton Smith">
NATO's outgoing commander in Bosnia, Admiral Leighton Smith, on Wednesday was awarded the NATO medal for his work in overseeing the alliance's 60,000- strong peace mission, its biggest-ever ground operation. "You have made an outstanding contribution to peace on this continent," NATO Secretary-General Javier Solana told a large crowd of officials, family and friends at a sun-drenched ceremony outside NATO's sprawling Brussels headquarters.
<p>
Solana was flanked by NATO's Supreme Allied Commander in Europe General George Joulwan and the chairman of the alliance's military committee General Klaus Naumann. Smith will formally hand over his duties to his successor Admiral Joseph Lopez on July 31 at NATO's southern command headquarters -- rear base for the huge air, sea and land operation in Bosnia -- before taking retirement.<br>
</td>
</table>


<br><br>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<img src="background.gif" alt="To learn more..." align=bottom border=0><br>
