<META Name="keywords" Content=
"Bosnia Herzegovina Serbia Croatia Former Yugoslavia 
Kosovo cattle foot and mouth disease emergency 
Kacanik Strpci Kosovska Vitina Prizren">

<HEAD>
<title>BERSERKISTAN IN BOSNIA: Foot and Mouth Epidemic Emergency Declared in Kosovo</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#454545" link="#A62A2A" vlink="#B87333">

<BODY>
<blockquote>
<img src="flat280.gif" width=280 height=119 
align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 alt="BERSERKISTAN">
<br>
<hr size=1 align=left>

<TABLE WIDTH=550 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=15>
<TD WIDTH=88 valign=top align=right>
<font size=1>
<img src="navigator.gif" USEMAP="#navigator" 
width=80 height=256 alt="Berserkistan Navigator" hspace=0 
vspace=2 align=bottom border=0></td>

<TD valign=top align=left>
<FONT SIZE=6><b>
Foot and Mouth Epidemic<br>
Emergency Declared <br>
in Kosovo Province</b>
<font size=4>
<p>
<b>The entire southern province of Kosovo has been declared an endangered zone</b>
<p>
<font size=2>
<img src="m_kosovo.gif" width=262 height=207 
vspace=5 hspace=0 alt="Kosovo Province" align=left border=0>
BELGRADE, July 13 (Reuter) - Yugoslav authorities have declared a state of emergency in four regions contaminated with foot-and-mouth livestock disease, the official news agency Tanjug said on Saturday. The entire southern province of Kosovo has been declared an "endangered zone," it added. Four municipalities along the southern border region with Albania and Macedonia have been named as infected: Kacanik, Strpci, Kosovska Vitina and Prizren.
<p>
Tanjug said people living there have been advised to cancel or at least restrict any trips to stop the virus from spreading. It was not imediately clear how many infected animals have been found, although one report said fewer than 100 head of cattle had been destroyed. Earlier, the independent Beta news agency reported that 360 veterinary officers had been sent to Kosovo to examine herds and slaughter any animals suspected of having the virus.
<p>
In the past few weeks, foot-and-mouth disease has appeared in Albania, Macedonia and Greece. The border region between Yugoslavia and Albania is mountainous and ethnic Albanians on both sides share cattle herds. Farmers along the Macedonian border also often allow their herds to graze freely.
<p>
Livestock markets have been closed in several Kosovo municipalities and the authorities have banned farmers from grazing cattle outside enclosed grazing land. The World Veterinarian Organisation proclaimed Yugoslavia free of foot and mouth disease in 1974.


</td>
</table>


